■ Car Price Prediction Web App
This is a simple Flask web application that predicts car prices based on user inputs like car length, width, height,
engine size, horsepower, and peak RPM. It uses a pre-trained machine learning model (model_1.pkl) for making
predictions.
■ Project Structure
car-price-predictor/ ■■■ app.py # Main Flask application ■■■ model_1.pkl # Pre-trained ML model
(pickled) ■■■ templates/ ■ ■■■ index.html # HTML form for input ■■■ static/ # (Optional) CSS or
image files ■■■ README.md # Project documentation
■■ Technologies Used
- Python
- Flask
- scikit-learn
- HTML (for frontend form)
- Pickle (for model serialization)
■ Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/yourusername/car-price-predictor.git cd
car-price-predictor 2. (Optional) Create and activate a virtual environment: python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate 3. Install required dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt If not available: pip install flask numpy scikit-learn 4. Ensure
model_1.pkl is in the project root. 5. Run the app: python app.py 6. Open your browser and go to:
http://127.0.0.1:5000/
■ Features
- Simple user interface
- Real-time predictions
- Easy to deploy locally or in the cloud
■ Model Input Features
- carlength (float)
- carwidth (float)
- carheight (float)
- enginesize (float)
- horsepower (float)
- peakrpm (float)
■ Example Usage
Input: carlength: 180.0 carwidth: 65.0 carheight: 54.0 enginesize: 130 horsepower: 110 peakrpm:
5500 Output: Predicted Price: 15400.0
